{
  "stem": "14168.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was more than a small fortune, at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- it was worth, I would say, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in today's terms, at least $4,000-- the purchasing power, that kind of money.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for Europe, for people, who were practically stranded, who-- who were doomed, it was just like a lifeline.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's what it was for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a-- it was just the difference between survival and doom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right, we're talking about November 1938, right after the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "While I was in Berlin, fleeing from the Nazis in Breslau, I tried to make as much use of-- of my time, in practical terms, trying to find some way of getting out of Germany as I could.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there I had found that the Palestine and Orient Lloyd, which was a Jewish travel bureau, was-- offered people the possibility of getting out of Europe, if they had enough money for visas to South America.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how I landed in that office, and I got-- I was told what I had to do in order to get the visa.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a tourist visa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You had to buy round-trip ticket because otherwise, people would never let you on board a ship.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so that's what I did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that place was full, that office in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I still remember it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was next to the Zionist headquarters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was-- you couldn't even say standing room only.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Most people didn't have the money or didn't have the connection that I had at the time or were turned down by their relatives.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I finally-- I got the-- I got a passport.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, getting my passport, I had to apply to the passport office in Breslau of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
